'''Ahmed Mohammed Al-Ganehi''' ([[Arabic]]: أَحْمَد مُحَمَّد الْجَانِحِيّ) (born 22 September 2000) is a Qatari professional [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|winger]] for [[Qatar Stars League]] club  [[Al-Gharafa SC|Al-Gharafa]]<ref name="mundial11">{{cite web|url=https://app.mundial11.com/players/4w69jqzykx9e7noz|title=Ahmed Al Ganehi|author=XS Studios|publisher=www.mundial11.ae|accessdate=2020-06-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/ahmed-alganehi/576187/|title=Qatar - Ahmed Al Ganehi - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|website=us.soccerway.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kooora.com/?player=140940|title=اللاعب : أحمد محمد الجانحي|website=www.kooora.com}}</ref> and the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].

==Career==
Al-Ganehi started his career at [[Al-Gharafa SC|Al-Gharafa]] and is a product of the Aspire Academy's youth system. On 23 February 2019, Al Ganehi made his professional debut for Al-Gharafa against [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]] in the Pro League, replacing [[Ahmed Alaaeldin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الغرافة يتعادل سلبياً مع الدحيل|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/02/23/qatar/stars-league/al-gharrafa-club-doha-/al-shorta/2967939/}}</ref>

